# Rule: .agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md

A skill is a **procedure**, not a rule. It must:

- have frontmatter with `name`, `when to use`, `procedure`, `outputs`;
- show the procedure as numbered steps;
- end with a "Done when" or "Outputs" section that lets a reviewer or the
  agent itself verify completion;
- be loaded **by name** when relevant, not on every task (per the
  `when to use` field).

## Template

```markdown
---
name: <kebab-case>
when to use: <one sentence — the trigger>
procedure: <n steps>
outputs: <what the procedure produces, in concrete file paths / artifacts>
---

# Skill: <name>

> <one paragraph>

## Inputs
<what the agent must have read or know before starting>

## Procedure
1. …
2. …

## Outputs
- <artefact 1>
- <artefact 2>

## Done when
- [ ] …
```
